WEBVTT

00:54.360 --> 00:55.094
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

00:55.094 --> 00:55.894
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

00:55.894 --> 00:56.595
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

00:56.595 --> 00:57.296
(for filming child actors and animals.)

01:15.224 --> 01:16.592
Do you want to go get some air?

01:17.159 --> 01:18.627
My morning's pretty open.

01:20.329 --> 01:22.131
On the phone you gave me,

01:24.233 --> 01:25.868
there aren't any numbers saved.

01:29.071 --> 01:30.506
It's completely empty.

01:31.440 --> 01:32.474
Just like me.

01:38.581 --> 01:41.217
Your old phone...

01:41.217 --> 01:43.385
and the bag with your wallet in it
are missing.

01:43.886 --> 01:44.753
You probably...

01:45.521 --> 01:48.657
lost them at the convenience store
where that little thief works.

01:49.792 --> 01:52.661
I already reported it, so they'll call.

01:57.433 --> 01:59.401
If I committed some kind of crime,

02:00.769 --> 02:02.705
just tell me. It's okay.

02:07.042 --> 02:09.778
You don't need to worry about
what those detectives said.

02:11.914 --> 02:14.216
They were just leading you on
to get the answer they wanted and...

02:14.216 --> 02:15.017
No.

02:15.284 --> 02:16.952
When I was talking to the detectives,

02:17.419 --> 02:19.221
my heart was pounding so hard...

02:19.221 --> 02:20.556
that I wanted to run out of there.

02:21.590 --> 02:23.859
There has to be a reason I feel this way.

02:26.262 --> 02:27.029
Myo Jin.

02:27.329 --> 02:29.899
Right now, the best thing
is for you to focus on treatment.

02:29.899 --> 02:31.433
And what exactly
does "the best thing" mean?

02:32.434 --> 02:33.736
You know...

02:33.736 --> 02:35.337
what happened to me, Jun Ho.

02:36.438 --> 02:37.973
You can see how frustrated I am.

02:37.973 --> 02:39.775
So why won't you just tell me everything?

02:46.148 --> 02:47.816
I talked it over with Dr. Jung.

02:48.417 --> 02:51.053
I asked whether it might help...

02:51.420 --> 02:54.290
if you tried, even little by little,

02:54.290 --> 02:55.991
to recall memories
connected to the accident.

02:55.991 --> 02:56.892
That's right.

02:57.660 --> 02:59.028
That's exactly what I think.

02:59.295 --> 03:00.996
But the answer was the opposite.

03:02.164 --> 03:04.099
Talking about the accident...

03:05.467 --> 03:06.402
could actually...

03:06.969 --> 03:09.205
have a negative effect
on your state of mind.

03:09.839 --> 03:13.175
And that would only slow normal recovery.

03:13.442 --> 03:14.310
Really?

03:15.544 --> 03:17.379
So the reason
you can't tell me anything...

03:18.948 --> 03:20.449
is because it's all for my sake?

03:20.916 --> 03:22.051
Think carefully.

03:22.751 --> 03:24.687
You seem to be in danger right now.

03:25.221 --> 03:27.590
Instead of trying
to recover your memories,

03:27.590 --> 03:29.458
if you focus only on your emotions,

03:29.458 --> 03:31.927
things will only become
more complicated and confusing.

03:32.728 --> 03:34.029
That way of thinking is dangerous.

03:34.763 --> 03:36.031
Emotions...

03:36.031 --> 03:37.766
should be seen as a means to an end.

03:38.834 --> 03:40.135
A means to an end?

03:40.469 --> 03:43.138
When you're trying to recover your memory,
everything becomes a means to that end.

03:44.206 --> 03:47.810
Not just your own sensations,
feelings, and thoughts,

03:48.711 --> 03:50.145
but everything around you.

03:52.548 --> 03:54.517
How far...

03:54.517 --> 03:56.418
am I supposed to take that?

03:56.952 --> 03:59.722
That depends on how you choose to see it.

04:00.523 --> 04:02.091
Then that means...

04:03.726 --> 04:05.227
my fiancé...

04:06.028 --> 04:07.630
would be included too, right?

04:08.230 --> 04:10.166
If that's how you see it, Ms. Ham.

04:16.205 --> 04:17.173
Thank you...

04:18.908 --> 04:20.476
for that advice...

04:21.243 --> 04:23.345
that I shouldn't trust anyone
until I get my memory back.

04:24.013 --> 04:27.183
Whether you trust someone or not
is your choice, Ms. Ham,

04:27.583 --> 04:29.218
but there's one thing you mustn't forget.

04:29.618 --> 04:30.586
What is it?

04:30.853 --> 04:32.822
If you don't trust someone,

04:33.355 --> 04:36.091
that person won't trust you, either.

04:38.194 --> 04:39.195
That could become...

04:40.329 --> 04:42.331
my biggest obstacle.

04:45.348 --> 04:48.117
(Distrust)

05:43.005 --> 05:44.073
"H."

05:49.078 --> 05:50.079
Hee Su.

05:52.315 --> 05:53.349
Choi Hee Su.

06:04.894 --> 06:06.462
(Certificate of Resident Registration)

06:06.462 --> 06:08.731
(Ryu Jun Ho, Ham Myo Jin)

06:14.771 --> 06:15.471
(Seoyeon-dong Community Service Center)

06:15.471 --> 06:18.474
Please insert your card
into the slot in the correct direction.

06:27.383 --> 06:29.619
"263, Gahan-ro."

06:38.661 --> 06:39.428
It's a gift.

06:40.062 --> 06:41.030
(National Forensic Service)

06:45.034 --> 06:46.369
At the Jebudo Island villa,

06:46.936 --> 06:48.805
they found the weapon used in the crime.

06:49.572 --> 06:50.440
A weapon?

06:51.641 --> 06:52.542
A crime?

06:53.342 --> 06:56.012
Our whole direction in the investigation
has been completely wrong.

06:57.647 --> 06:59.415
I looked over
the initial autopsy results again,

06:59.415 --> 07:00.750
and both of the deceased...

07:00.950 --> 07:02.819
were listed as having died in the fire.

07:04.821 --> 07:07.557
It's been long since the accident,
and only now...

07:08.257 --> 07:09.659
Did you ever imagine...

07:11.127 --> 07:13.596
someone could commit murder
in that blazing inferno?

07:30.513 --> 07:32.849
I'm Ryu Jun Ho. I work in architecture.

07:34.083 --> 07:35.718
I'm sorry for coming here so abruptly.

08:03.179 --> 08:04.647
Only a few people at the top...

08:04.647 --> 08:06.983
know that I'm serving as a judge,

08:08.317 --> 08:10.086
so I suppose someone has a loose tongue.

08:12.155 --> 08:13.556
If you knew about me in advance,

08:15.525 --> 08:18.194
then you must also be aware
of the qualifications to be announced.

08:19.095 --> 08:22.465
Applicants must hold
a Korean architect's license...

08:23.065 --> 08:25.134
and have at least ten years...

08:25.134 --> 08:26.903
of practical experience
in architectural design.

08:26.903 --> 08:27.770
However,

08:29.005 --> 08:31.607
I don't meet that requirement.

08:32.341 --> 08:33.609
This is a project...

08:33.609 --> 08:35.812
to build the largest museum in Asia.

08:37.079 --> 08:39.382
The project seems far too large...

08:39.382 --> 08:41.184
to take on with ambition alone.

08:42.051 --> 08:43.085
Of course,

08:43.085 --> 08:45.321
I understand why you'd think that.

08:45.321 --> 08:46.622
As you know,

08:48.458 --> 08:52.562
most of the great architects
since the 20th century...

08:53.095 --> 08:55.965
only produced their signature works
after turning 40.

08:57.300 --> 08:59.001
There will still be...

09:00.336 --> 09:01.337
many opportunities ahead.

09:01.704 --> 09:03.940
If you would give me that opportunity,

09:03.940 --> 09:04.774
I'm confident...

09:06.209 --> 09:07.844
I can surprise you, sir.

09:11.180 --> 09:13.516
I will bring you a design for this museum.

09:14.684 --> 09:17.587
And if there's even
the slightest resemblance...

09:17.587 --> 09:20.423
to any museum you've ever seen
or can remember,

09:20.423 --> 09:21.891
I'll withdraw that very moment.

09:22.125 --> 09:24.193
I'm sure everyone else
is preparing with that same resolve.

09:24.193 --> 09:25.428
At the official judging,

09:25.428 --> 09:27.130
I'll submit a different design.

09:27.130 --> 09:28.431
Likewise,

09:28.431 --> 09:31.033
if it isn't a museum
you've truly never seen before,

09:32.301 --> 09:33.903
please eliminate me on the spot.

09:34.303 --> 09:36.873
I suggest you think very carefully.

09:36.873 --> 09:37.774
you still seem too young for this.

09:37.774 --> 09:40.810
Even the world-renowned architects
you mentioned...

09:41.444 --> 09:42.411
must have had a time,

09:43.045 --> 09:44.514
like me now,

09:44.514 --> 09:46.549
when they struggled to prove themselves.

09:46.549 --> 09:47.517
And...

09:47.884 --> 09:50.086
there must have been one person
who recognized that effort.

09:50.086 --> 09:51.087
Right now,

09:52.722 --> 09:54.223
I desperately need that one person too.

10:01.731 --> 10:02.899
Mr. Ryu.

10:04.333 --> 10:05.168
Yes?

10:06.602 --> 10:07.837
What's the name of your firm?

10:09.705 --> 10:11.107
Mono Architecture.

10:11.741 --> 10:12.575
Mono?

10:14.143 --> 10:15.445
The Mono I know?

10:36.999 --> 10:37.834
Myo Jin.

10:38.167 --> 10:39.235
It's been such a long time.

10:41.637 --> 10:44.173
Yeah, it's been a while.

10:45.007 --> 10:47.510
You two seriously hurt me.

10:47.510 --> 10:49.745
How could you both
cut off contact at the same time?

10:50.179 --> 10:51.147
I'm honestly offended.

10:52.315 --> 10:53.549
Actually,

10:53.549 --> 10:55.885
I was sick for a while.

10:55.885 --> 10:57.386
So I was taking some time off.

10:57.386 --> 10:58.688
Really?

10:59.589 --> 11:01.157
Then what about the rich lady?

11:02.625 --> 11:04.927
You mean Hee Su, right?

11:04.927 --> 11:06.195
Of course.

11:06.195 --> 11:07.763
Who else would I mean besides you two?

11:09.432 --> 11:10.299
Well,

11:11.400 --> 11:13.536
Hee Su wasn't feeling well either,
so she was hospitalized.

11:13.536 --> 11:14.637
Seriously?

11:14.904 --> 11:16.305
You two were that close,

11:16.873 --> 11:18.374
and even got sick at the same time.

11:21.778 --> 11:24.380
So I guess
you'll be alone at the studio for a while.

11:25.214 --> 11:26.115
The studio?

11:26.315 --> 11:27.116
Yeah.

11:27.116 --> 11:29.452
You two painted together
at the studio every day.

11:29.852 --> 11:31.220
Aren't you headed there even now?

11:42.131 --> 11:43.933
Your fingerprint is registered here.

11:43.933 --> 11:45.668
How could you forget this place?

11:45.902 --> 11:47.770
I was just confused for a second.

11:47.770 --> 11:49.071
I remember now.

11:50.239 --> 11:51.674
Okay.

11:57.213 --> 11:58.514
I've never seen this painting before.

11:59.715 --> 12:00.783
You're the one on the right, right?

12:05.254 --> 12:06.989
Since it says "H,"

12:07.623 --> 12:09.592
the rich lady painted it.

12:16.499 --> 12:18.234
I should get going.

12:18.501 --> 12:19.535
You'll come again, right?

12:20.536 --> 12:23.773
After you're done,
do you have time to talk to me?

12:23.773 --> 12:24.907
Time?

12:24.907 --> 12:25.808
Why?

12:27.009 --> 12:30.113
I wanted to ask you about Hee Su.

12:30.113 --> 12:31.814
Ask me?

12:32.415 --> 12:33.950
You were the one closest to her,

12:33.950 --> 12:35.551
so what could you possibly want to ask me?

12:37.487 --> 12:39.455
I really have to go.

12:40.756 --> 12:41.824
Okay.

12:43.092 --> 12:43.993
But...

12:44.494 --> 12:46.429
this painting is really good.

12:46.696 --> 12:48.364
You two are really talented.

13:00.643 --> 13:03.146
You didn't come because you missed me,

13:18.928 --> 13:19.762
so why?

13:20.096 --> 13:21.964
Did something come up
that you want to ask me?

13:24.167 --> 13:26.536
That's right, I remember.

13:28.838 --> 13:29.739
Hee Su.

13:32.809 --> 13:34.610
We were definitely together.

13:40.917 --> 13:42.251
Come on.

13:47.156 --> 13:49.125
Hey, isn't it ridiculous?

13:49.725 --> 13:51.494
Nobody knows about this place.

13:52.462 --> 13:53.396
No way.

13:53.729 --> 13:55.631
It's this nice,
so why doesn't anyone know?

13:56.232 --> 13:58.968
Are you secretly
keeping people from coming here?

14:00.670 --> 14:02.205
Honestly, I wish I were.

14:03.272 --> 14:04.574
Is there some way?

14:05.608 --> 14:07.376
You could ask your dad...

14:07.376 --> 14:10.012
to build another villa here.

14:10.279 --> 14:12.882
Then this whole area would
basically become your own private beach.

14:13.749 --> 14:16.119
Ham Myo Jin.

14:16.986 --> 14:18.221
You're a genius.

14:19.288 --> 14:21.190
My dad would totally do that much.

14:21.457 --> 14:22.425
Seriously?

14:22.792 --> 14:23.926
Of course.

14:24.260 --> 14:25.261
Hey.

14:25.261 --> 14:27.497
Are you saying that
knowing what kind of person my dad is?

14:28.664 --> 14:31.934
You sound like you know
exactly what he's like.

14:33.236 --> 14:34.737
I was kidding.

14:35.471 --> 14:36.739
Don't say this to him.

14:36.739 --> 14:38.307
He'll think I'm weird.

14:42.211 --> 14:44.547
Wait.
He probably still doesn't know who I am.

14:45.448 --> 14:46.382
He does.

14:47.416 --> 14:48.718
I've already told him about you.

14:49.085 --> 14:50.353
He says he wants to meet you too.

14:51.254 --> 14:52.088
Really?

14:52.255 --> 14:53.122
Yeah.

14:53.122 --> 14:55.591
He said once he's back,
we should all go on vacation together.

14:56.392 --> 14:57.827
That sounds fun.

14:57.827 --> 14:58.928
I could introduce myself to him.

14:59.695 --> 15:01.030
But who knows.

15:01.430 --> 15:04.133
His schedule is all over the place.

15:04.934 --> 15:07.270
So you have no idea when he'll be back?

15:07.837 --> 15:10.740
Yeah. Sometimes he just suddenly shows up.

15:12.141 --> 15:14.644
And he still hasn't said
when he's coming back?

15:14.944 --> 15:15.812
Hey.

15:16.145 --> 15:17.713
Why are you so curious...

15:17.713 --> 15:19.015
about when my dad's coming back?

15:20.016 --> 15:21.784
You ask every chance you get.

15:23.453 --> 15:24.687
It's just...

15:29.625 --> 15:32.395
Let's not make a good relationship
awkward for no reason.

15:33.296 --> 15:35.298
I want to stay your friend.

15:36.165 --> 15:38.101
I don't want to become family.

15:39.769 --> 15:40.770
What are you even saying?

15:42.038 --> 15:43.506
Though that would be kind of funny too.

15:44.440 --> 15:46.576
You giving birth to my younger sibling.

15:48.044 --> 15:49.612
Then I can call you "Mom," right?

15:50.980 --> 15:51.814
Hey!

15:52.148 --> 15:53.816
Mom!

15:54.150 --> 15:55.751
Get over here!

15:55.751 --> 15:58.454
Mom, I want a little brother.

15:58.955 --> 16:00.189
Mom.

16:14.604 --> 16:16.839
Your old phone...

16:16.839 --> 16:18.875
and the bag with your wallet in it
are missing.

16:19.509 --> 16:20.510
You probably...

16:21.043 --> 16:24.147
lost them at the convenience store
where that little thief works.

16:33.823 --> 16:34.757
Hey.

16:34.757 --> 16:35.825
Hey.

16:36.859 --> 16:38.094
That woman came again.

16:43.032 --> 16:44.367
We should talk for a minute.

17:01.751 --> 17:02.752
How'd you know...

17:03.619 --> 17:04.620
I took it?

17:04.954 --> 17:06.556
If you hadn't listened again today,

17:06.556 --> 17:07.990
you would've ended up
at the police station again.

17:08.357 --> 17:09.292
Whatever.

17:11.327 --> 17:12.562
But is that rumor true?

17:13.729 --> 17:14.764
About the murder?

17:16.966 --> 17:18.067
Be honest with me.

17:19.402 --> 17:21.104
Who exactly are they saying I killed?

17:22.205 --> 17:23.406
What are you talking about?

17:24.273 --> 17:25.408
I mean that guy.

17:25.408 --> 17:27.276
The one who tried to hit me
at the police station.

17:28.077 --> 17:28.945
What?

17:31.214 --> 17:32.582
Jun Ho?

17:32.815 --> 17:34.750
You saw my mom causing a scene
at the police station, right?

17:36.719 --> 17:38.321
They say that guy is seriously scary.

17:40.223 --> 17:41.190
No way.

17:41.557 --> 17:43.960
Didn't the chairman
of the company he works for die recently?

17:45.628 --> 17:47.597
He burned to death in his sleep
when the villa exploded.

17:48.998 --> 17:50.199
And wasn't that chairman super rich?

17:52.468 --> 17:53.736
If he had nothing to do
with that accident,

17:53.736 --> 17:55.238
why would the police
show up at his house...

17:56.038 --> 17:57.340
again and again?

17:57.340 --> 17:58.641
You know...

17:58.641 --> 18:00.309
what happened to me, Jun Ho.

18:00.543 --> 18:01.978
You can see how frustrated I am,

18:01.978 --> 18:03.780
so why won't you just tell me everything?

18:04.313 --> 18:07.116
Right now, the best thing
is for you to focus on treatment.

18:07.116 --> 18:08.818
This is a time to be careful.

18:09.819 --> 18:10.753
Don't...

18:11.654 --> 18:13.089
overinterpret everything.

18:13.756 --> 18:15.525
Do you think locking your door
will stop rumors from spreading?

18:15.992 --> 18:18.127
What, do you think
everyone around here is stupid?

18:18.628 --> 18:21.230
I heard you got in a car accident
back then and hit your head.

18:22.832 --> 18:24.434
That's why you were
in the hospital all this time.

18:26.969 --> 18:29.972
So people are talking about me too?

18:30.306 --> 18:31.207
Are you some attention seeker?

18:33.109 --> 18:35.711
Why would anyone care
about someone who doesn't even live here?

18:35.978 --> 18:37.346
I don't live here?

18:37.346 --> 18:38.815
That's enough.

18:39.182 --> 18:41.617
If you're that curious,
go ask at the police station.

18:48.891 --> 18:49.859
Where's my phone?

18:50.159 --> 18:51.027
What phone?

18:53.129 --> 18:54.230
That's all there is.

18:55.364 --> 18:56.299
Give it.

19:43.312 --> 19:44.180
Mono?

19:45.715 --> 19:47.049
The Mono I know?

19:47.250 --> 19:48.351
Yes, that's right.

19:50.820 --> 19:52.922
Chairman Choi Young Ho
mentioned you to me a few times,

19:52.922 --> 19:54.824
but I never expected
to see you here like this.

19:55.224 --> 19:56.092
Excuse me?

19:56.292 --> 19:58.394
People had all sorts of things to say,

19:58.394 --> 20:00.530
but he had exceptional instincts.

20:01.731 --> 20:04.834
Bringing renowned foreign designers
onto an advisory board...

20:05.601 --> 20:08.137
and having them involved
from the earliest design stage...

20:08.137 --> 20:10.573
was first introduced in Korea
by Chairman Choi.

20:10.973 --> 20:13.276
I was overseas
when I heard about the accident,

20:14.143 --> 20:15.778
so I wasn't able
to pay my respects properly.

20:18.214 --> 20:19.215
I'm sorry.

20:19.749 --> 20:23.519
I had no idea...

20:23.519 --> 20:24.954
Chairman Choi and you knew each other.

20:24.954 --> 20:26.022
If I had known,

20:27.390 --> 20:29.325
I never would've come here like this.

20:29.792 --> 20:32.495
Please pretend today never happened.

20:34.597 --> 20:35.465
Mr. Ryu.

20:36.165 --> 20:36.999
Yes?

20:37.733 --> 20:39.836
Do I strike you as someone
who's swayed by what others say?

20:42.472 --> 20:45.408
I've never done anything
that didn't move my heart.

20:46.309 --> 20:48.111
And that's still true now.

20:48.511 --> 20:50.179
I've always wondered...

20:50.179 --> 20:52.915
what kind of person you were...

20:52.915 --> 20:54.317
for Chairman Choi to praise you so highly.

20:55.218 --> 20:57.186
What you showed me here today...

20:57.186 --> 20:59.956
has only made me more curious.

21:00.623 --> 21:03.192
What the late chairman said...

21:04.026 --> 21:06.095
and the judgment I'm making now...

21:06.095 --> 21:07.163
are two different things.

21:10.199 --> 21:12.802
Let me see your work, Mr. Ryu.

21:14.604 --> 21:15.872
Come to my studio.

21:30.620 --> 21:31.721
You're here.

21:33.790 --> 21:35.158
There's something I want to know.

21:36.125 --> 21:36.926
Yeah?

21:37.527 --> 21:38.361
What?

21:41.531 --> 21:42.765
I want to know who she is.

21:50.306 --> 21:51.174
Her?

21:51.707 --> 21:52.942
She's your friend.

21:54.243 --> 21:55.244
What kind of friend?

21:56.245 --> 21:57.413
What do you mean, what kind?

21:59.115 --> 22:02.385
Just the kind of ordinary friend
anyone might have.

22:02.952 --> 22:04.720
Her name is Hee Su, right?

22:05.922 --> 22:06.856
I'm not sure.

22:07.690 --> 22:10.259
I don't think she was
that important a friend.

22:11.394 --> 22:12.395
Really?

22:15.465 --> 22:17.333
Can we talk later?

22:17.333 --> 22:19.368
I need to wrap this up and head out.

22:22.505 --> 22:23.706
Get some rest.

22:23.706 --> 22:24.740
You look tired.

22:30.947 --> 22:31.948
So...

22:33.716 --> 22:35.618
you really don't know this woman?

22:39.222 --> 22:40.123
Why?

22:40.590 --> 22:43.693
Is she on your mind that much?

22:47.463 --> 22:48.364
No.

22:49.365 --> 22:50.933
Like you said, Jun Ho,

22:50.933 --> 22:52.668
I hope we weren't that close either.

23:14.290 --> 23:17.293
(Special Sale, Bread, Buy 1 Get 1)

23:57.033 --> 23:57.967
Hey.

23:59.402 --> 24:00.470
Sorry.

24:03.573 --> 24:06.943
But I'm hungry.

24:19.922 --> 24:20.890
Eat this.

24:22.225 --> 24:23.659
Thank you.

24:33.402 --> 24:34.871
Thank you.

24:48.151 --> 24:49.352
I know.

24:49.352 --> 24:51.821
I know what a good man you are.

24:52.321 --> 24:54.223
I know that better than anyone.

24:55.358 --> 24:57.560
But what does that get you?

24:57.560 --> 24:58.928
Does anybody give you
some kind of medal for it?

25:10.573 --> 25:12.275
Do you think that woman
is going to leave you alone...

25:13.142 --> 25:14.944
when you know
every single thing there is to know?

25:16.345 --> 25:17.980
What, are you going to regret it...

25:17.980 --> 25:19.682
only after someone
puts a knife through your neck?

25:19.982 --> 25:22.385
They're not the kind of people
to let this end here.

25:50.213 --> 25:51.047
Myo Jin.

25:55.685 --> 25:56.486
Jun Ho?

26:08.498 --> 26:09.665
- I'm sorry.
- What?

26:09.665 --> 26:12.268
Work had me way too on edge earlier.

26:13.002 --> 26:15.438
I couldn't even give you a proper answer.

26:17.774 --> 26:19.909
Did you come back just to tell me that?

26:23.246 --> 26:25.047
They're monsters in human skin.

26:25.915 --> 26:28.384
If you keep dragging your feet,
someone's going to bleed again.

26:29.752 --> 26:31.988
If you don't want to end up
in real trouble,

26:31.988 --> 26:34.590
you need to move right now
before it comes back on you.

26:36.425 --> 26:38.594
Just trust me and follow my lead.

26:39.095 --> 26:41.297
You've never lost out
by listening to me before, have you?

26:56.112 --> 26:56.979
So?

27:00.817 --> 27:01.818
Hey.

27:05.688 --> 27:08.057
What's this plan of yours?

27:11.093 --> 27:13.296
What could be so important...

27:13.296 --> 27:15.031
that we can't even be together
this late at night?

27:15.798 --> 27:16.632
Right?

27:17.233 --> 27:18.468
Don't do that anymore.

27:19.235 --> 27:21.838
Even if something's bothering me,
we can talk about it later.

27:22.205 --> 27:23.072
Okay.

27:23.873 --> 27:24.707
I'm sorry.

27:26.809 --> 27:28.845
But aren't you late?

27:28.845 --> 27:30.246
No, it's okay.

27:30.246 --> 27:31.848
I pushed it back a little.

27:32.181 --> 27:33.116
I won't be late.

27:37.019 --> 27:38.221
About what you asked earlier,

27:39.188 --> 27:40.590
something came back to me.

27:41.657 --> 27:42.492
What?

27:43.025 --> 27:44.494
That friend, Choi Hee Su.

27:47.063 --> 27:47.997
I feel like...

27:48.898 --> 27:52.135
there were times
she was kind of rough with you.

27:53.102 --> 27:54.937
So I don't think I saw her after that.

27:57.140 --> 27:58.908
What happened?

28:01.477 --> 28:03.746
I don't remember clearly,

28:05.448 --> 28:07.150
but maybe I should say
she was harsh with her words.

28:11.954 --> 28:14.423
I don't remember...

28:15.191 --> 28:16.659
anything like that at all.

28:18.795 --> 28:19.862
But Myo Jin.

28:21.764 --> 28:22.598
Yes?

28:23.833 --> 28:26.436
What made you think
of that friend, Hee Su?

28:28.171 --> 28:29.939
And where did that photo come from?

28:33.209 --> 28:35.077
I ran into a friend at the hospital.

28:35.912 --> 28:36.813
A friend?

28:37.613 --> 28:38.481
Yes.

28:39.348 --> 28:41.617
We only asked how each other was doing,
and then went our separate ways,

28:41.617 --> 28:43.085
so we didn't talk long.

28:44.020 --> 28:46.589
I see.
I guess you all knew each other well.

28:48.391 --> 28:49.559
I guess so.

28:51.794 --> 28:52.995
Did you get their contact information?

28:54.430 --> 28:56.032
Invite them over sometime.

28:58.701 --> 29:00.903
I gave my number.

29:03.773 --> 29:04.941
I'd like to meet that friend too...

29:05.842 --> 29:06.943
and see what kind of person they are.

29:09.579 --> 29:11.114
I'll say you said that if I get a call.

29:12.515 --> 29:13.349
Okay.

29:16.385 --> 29:18.354
I should get going now.

29:35.271 --> 29:36.472
I want to know who she is.

29:37.673 --> 29:38.574
So...

29:40.376 --> 29:42.211
you really don't know this woman?

30:18.815 --> 30:22.351
(No Entry - Under Investigation)

30:55.284 --> 30:56.853
This villa's burned to the ground.

30:57.687 --> 30:58.855
What brings you here?

31:01.124 --> 31:02.191
Hello.

31:02.558 --> 31:03.759
It looks like you're from Seoul.

31:04.393 --> 31:05.628
What brings you all the way out here?

31:09.065 --> 31:10.233
I'm sorry,

31:10.666 --> 31:12.568
but it's been a while
since I've been here,

31:12.869 --> 31:14.670
so I was wondering
if you happen to know me.

31:16.172 --> 31:17.907
I'm the village chief.

31:18.274 --> 31:20.910
This villa belongs to
the chairman's daughter.

31:21.778 --> 31:22.779
The chairman?

31:23.746 --> 31:25.882
You don't know
Chairman Choi of Mono Group?

31:26.149 --> 31:27.817
Don't you watch the news?

31:28.084 --> 31:29.819
That explosion happened at the villa,

31:29.819 --> 31:32.188
and it caused a stir.

31:32.188 --> 31:33.990
The chairman and his daughter both died.

31:35.992 --> 31:38.361
Do you know this woman by any chance?

31:39.562 --> 31:40.797
That's Ms. Choi,

31:41.764 --> 31:43.800
and the woman next to her is you.

31:45.535 --> 31:47.503
Do you know Hee Su well?

31:47.837 --> 31:49.639
No, not really.

31:50.373 --> 31:53.443
You should try that restaurant over there.

31:53.776 --> 31:56.245
The owner manages the villa too,

31:56.245 --> 31:57.480
and whenever Ms. Choi came,

31:57.480 --> 31:59.148
she'd bring meals up and all that.

32:00.917 --> 32:02.385
Okay.

32:04.287 --> 32:05.588
Poor them.

32:06.622 --> 32:08.591
That was taken
the last time you all came to visit.

32:08.591 --> 32:10.159
You all came in to eat together.

32:10.593 --> 32:13.095
Were there only three of us at the villa?

32:13.329 --> 32:14.697
Back then, yeah.

32:14.697 --> 32:16.532
And not long ago, you came by yourself.

32:16.966 --> 32:17.967
By myself?

32:17.967 --> 32:18.835
Yeah.

32:19.268 --> 32:21.137
You came to see Ms. Choi,

32:21.137 --> 32:22.338
but I told you she was out,

32:22.338 --> 32:23.940
and that you should wait here.

32:24.841 --> 32:25.708
Right.

32:25.708 --> 32:27.310
That's when you left your phone behind.

32:27.310 --> 32:28.144
Hold on.

32:28.311 --> 32:29.245
My phone?

32:29.245 --> 32:31.180
Yeah. Once you saw Ms. Choi coming back,

32:31.180 --> 32:32.782
you rushed out.

32:33.082 --> 32:34.984
Later, I saw you'd left your phone behind.

32:35.384 --> 32:37.186
I thought you'd come back for it
right away.

32:37.186 --> 32:37.954
Here it is.

32:39.522 --> 32:41.090
Then your accident happened
out of nowhere,

32:41.090 --> 32:42.825
and it completely slipped my mind.

32:45.661 --> 32:47.263
It's finally back with its owner.

32:48.631 --> 32:49.665
It doesn't work, does it?

32:50.066 --> 32:51.868
I turned it on a few times
to try and find you,

32:51.868 --> 32:52.902
but it didn't work.

32:53.636 --> 32:54.604
I see.

32:54.604 --> 32:56.506
Before it stopped working,

32:56.506 --> 32:58.674
there was one call from Seoul.

32:58.674 --> 33:00.843
They said it was important
and that you absolutely had to call back.

33:01.477 --> 33:03.379
Hold on, let me find the number.

33:03.379 --> 33:04.213
I put it right...

33:04.213 --> 33:05.381
Here it is.

33:06.616 --> 33:07.450
Here.

33:08.818 --> 33:11.053
(September)

33:31.874 --> 33:34.677
May I ask where this is?

33:35.211 --> 33:36.112
Here?

33:36.479 --> 33:37.480
It's a repair shop.

33:38.047 --> 33:38.981
Jigu Electronics.

33:40.016 --> 33:41.083
A repair shop?

33:44.120 --> 33:46.155
(Jigu Electronics)

33:46.556 --> 33:47.523
Goodness.

33:47.523 --> 33:50.626
I told you I'm not the type
to just run my mouth first.

33:50.626 --> 33:52.295
I'm a careful man.

33:52.295 --> 33:53.429
Deeply careful.

33:53.429 --> 33:55.565
Please don't make deep jokes like that.

33:55.565 --> 33:59.102
You definitely said
this laptop could be fixed.

33:59.102 --> 34:00.703
You said you'd make it...

34:00.703 --> 34:02.472
even more powerful
than those ONVIDIA graphics cards.

34:02.472 --> 34:03.706
But what is this?

34:03.706 --> 34:06.642
It's even glitchier now
than it was before the repair.

34:07.076 --> 34:08.010
I mean,

34:08.010 --> 34:09.345
the second I logged into the game,

34:09.345 --> 34:11.180
I just died right away.

34:11.180 --> 34:12.281
Bang, dead.

34:12.281 --> 34:14.484
Bang, dead.

34:14.484 --> 34:16.752
Of course, you're going to die.

34:16.752 --> 34:19.455
The graphics aren't the problem.

34:19.455 --> 34:20.957
When avatars start shooting each other,

34:20.957 --> 34:22.191
you're going to get shot too, right?

34:22.191 --> 34:23.326
How are you not supposed to get hit?

34:23.326 --> 34:25.428
You get shot, the zone closes in,
you run into enemies,

34:25.428 --> 34:26.429
and then once your energy runs out,

34:26.429 --> 34:28.164
you're out. Simple as that.

34:28.164 --> 34:31.868
That's why I told you
to find recovery items no matter what.

34:31.868 --> 34:34.403
Recovery items?

34:34.403 --> 34:36.239
You mean, like an energy drink?

34:36.239 --> 34:39.776
Energy drinks only restore 40 boost.

34:39.776 --> 34:40.610
What's the point of that?

34:40.610 --> 34:42.411
You stack a med kit on top of it,

34:42.411 --> 34:44.413
and then you shoot right up to 80.

34:44.781 --> 34:46.649
First, go buy those two items
and try again.

34:46.649 --> 34:47.884
And if you still die fast,

34:47.884 --> 34:50.186
then I'll personally teach you...

34:50.453 --> 34:52.188
the ultimate avatar strategy, okay?

34:53.689 --> 34:55.324
Okay. For real this time?

34:55.658 --> 34:56.726
Why can't you trust me?

34:56.726 --> 34:58.127
Go on, now. I'm busy.

34:58.861 --> 35:00.129
What was I supposed to do again?

35:00.563 --> 35:01.664
Sir.

35:02.365 --> 35:03.499
Promise to tell me the strategy.

35:03.499 --> 35:04.700
I promise.

35:04.700 --> 35:06.469
- There, stamped.
- Now get out of here.

35:06.469 --> 35:07.403
All right, I'm going.

35:10.440 --> 35:11.441
Hello.

35:12.008 --> 35:14.177
I was told you called my phone.

35:15.511 --> 35:17.180
What was it that you left here
to be repaired?

35:17.180 --> 35:18.781
Everything but batteries can be fixed.

35:18.781 --> 35:20.183
You'd have to buy a new battery,
that's why.

35:21.117 --> 35:22.285
It's just that...

35:22.285 --> 35:24.387
I can't really remember what I brought in.

35:24.387 --> 35:25.555
What are you talking about?

35:25.555 --> 35:26.923
How can you not remember
what you brought in?

35:28.257 --> 35:29.091
Wait.

35:30.092 --> 35:32.462
Myo...

35:32.462 --> 35:33.729
Ham Myo Jin.

35:33.729 --> 35:34.730
Do you know me?

35:34.730 --> 35:35.731
Of course, I do.

35:36.199 --> 35:38.668
But I heard you had a serious accident.

35:39.635 --> 35:40.837
Yes.

35:40.837 --> 35:43.239
I still can't remember things very well.

35:44.207 --> 35:45.374
You can't remember?

35:46.008 --> 35:47.176
That's bad.

35:47.176 --> 35:49.212
There's still quite a bit left for me
to collect on the balance.

35:49.979 --> 35:51.013
The balance?

35:51.747 --> 35:52.715
Money?

35:52.715 --> 35:53.850
What do I do now?

35:55.618 --> 35:57.920
Anyway, just come with me.

35:57.920 --> 35:58.921
Come on in.

35:59.789 --> 36:01.157
This really isn't good.

36:04.560 --> 36:05.695
Take a seat.

36:09.065 --> 36:10.032
But somehow,

36:10.700 --> 36:12.034
your whole vibe feels different.

36:12.769 --> 36:13.936
Maybe because it's been a while.

36:14.237 --> 36:15.037
Sorry?

36:15.037 --> 36:16.005
How do I put it?

36:16.005 --> 36:19.108
You've got this peaceful kind of vibe now,

36:19.108 --> 36:20.376
but also flex.

36:20.376 --> 36:21.344
No.

36:21.611 --> 36:23.946
Graceful, but elegant too.

36:23.946 --> 36:25.214
What was it I brought in?

36:26.015 --> 36:26.849
Wait.

36:29.886 --> 36:30.987
(Lee Sang Ho - National Police Agency)

36:38.628 --> 36:39.829
You didn't ask for a repair.

36:39.829 --> 36:40.930
You asked to look into a person.

36:41.631 --> 36:43.933
But are you sure you're okay?
You said you're still not yourself.

36:43.933 --> 36:45.968
It's fine. Just tell me.

36:46.502 --> 36:47.370
Okay.

36:47.370 --> 36:50.506
The pictures might be
a little hard to look at,

36:50.873 --> 36:51.941
but just take a look first.

36:52.675 --> 36:53.509
Here.

36:54.177 --> 36:55.244
This man here...

36:55.244 --> 36:56.779
is the one you hired me to investigate.

36:56.779 --> 36:58.714
He runs around with gangsters,

36:58.714 --> 37:01.017
does loan-sharking, violence,
and even dirty-fixer work.

37:01.017 --> 37:03.586
They're the kind of bastards who've done
every piece of trash work there is.

37:05.354 --> 37:07.757
I hired you to investigate
someone like that?

37:09.292 --> 37:10.426
You really don't remember, do you?

37:11.661 --> 37:13.830
His name is Lee Jong Su.
Forty-two years old.

37:13.830 --> 37:15.131
Single and unemployed.

37:15.131 --> 37:16.766
A hopeless,
bottom-of-the-barrel piece of garbage.

37:17.633 --> 37:18.901
But what's strange about him is,

37:18.901 --> 37:20.970
he used to have a perfectly decent job,

37:21.304 --> 37:22.672
then quit it overnight...

37:22.672 --> 37:24.674
and started running with thugs.

37:25.741 --> 37:28.678
The chauffeur
of the chairman of Mono Group...

37:28.678 --> 37:29.645
isn't some ordinary job.

37:30.146 --> 37:31.180
Mono Group?

37:31.180 --> 37:32.115
Yeah.

37:32.348 --> 37:35.751
Anyway, you asked me
for every bit of information on him.

37:35.751 --> 37:38.921
Personal details, relationships,
even where he lived.

37:42.325 --> 37:43.493
This is it.

37:43.493 --> 37:44.393
Thanks.

37:45.895 --> 37:47.330
Not long after I started working the case,

37:47.330 --> 37:49.365
I'd already figured out everything else.

37:49.365 --> 37:51.067
But I just couldn't pin down
where he was living.

37:51.567 --> 37:52.802
But where could he really go?

37:53.402 --> 37:55.471
It took some doing, but not long after,

37:55.471 --> 37:57.140
I picked up his trail
through a crypto exchange.

38:00.276 --> 38:01.677
It's gone up a lot.

38:01.677 --> 38:02.612
Thank you.

38:03.613 --> 38:04.547
You're leaving already?

38:04.847 --> 38:06.415
At first,
I thought maybe I'd seen it wrong.

38:06.849 --> 38:08.451
I figured he'd struck it big somewhere,

38:08.451 --> 38:10.052
because his whole look
had suddenly changed.

38:10.386 --> 38:12.288
In that short amount of time,
he became a completely different person.

38:13.055 --> 38:15.792
So I contacted you right away,

38:16.993 --> 38:18.027
but your accident happened.

38:18.528 --> 38:19.796
I was in a dilemma too.

38:20.096 --> 38:22.165
My client was in the hospital
hovering between life and death,

38:22.165 --> 38:24.133
but my conscience wouldn't let me drop it.

38:26.002 --> 38:28.137
Why did I want this man investigated?

38:28.438 --> 38:29.539
You forgot that too?

38:29.906 --> 38:31.307
You mentioned blackmail.

38:31.507 --> 38:33.142
Someone was blackmailing me?

38:33.142 --> 38:34.076
No.

38:34.410 --> 38:35.344
Blackmailing your friend, Ms. Ham.

38:36.679 --> 38:38.281
Your symptoms are really serious.

38:38.915 --> 38:40.716
How can every answer be wrong?

38:41.317 --> 38:43.386
What kind of blackmail
was this man using...

38:43.386 --> 38:44.921
that I even hired someone to look into it?

38:45.154 --> 38:48.825
You said he even went to the studio
where she painted and harassed her,

38:49.091 --> 38:51.327
and that it seemed strange...

38:51.327 --> 38:52.361
watching her just take it.

38:52.528 --> 38:54.163
When you tried to help her,

38:54.163 --> 38:55.965
you said your friend stopped you.

38:56.299 --> 38:57.700
Your friend's name was...

38:57.700 --> 38:59.435
Hee Su? Hee...

38:59.435 --> 39:00.403
Choi Hee Su!

39:00.403 --> 39:03.172
Why did I say I wanted to meet
the man blackmailing Hee Su?

39:04.140 --> 39:06.542
And why did Hee Su
stop me from helping her?

39:07.210 --> 39:09.812
Whether we go forward with it now or not,

39:10.213 --> 39:11.614
that's for you to decide, Ms. Ham.

39:11.614 --> 39:14.250
I didn't get to finish the job,
but you still owe me the balance.

39:14.250 --> 39:16.586
It took a lot of work to dig up this much.

39:19.789 --> 39:21.190
Start again, please.

39:21.190 --> 39:22.358
I'll text you my account number.

39:22.358 --> 39:23.392
Don't forget this.

39:23.392 --> 39:24.927
And there's hazard pay too.

39:24.927 --> 39:27.063
If I get physically hurt
or put in danger while investigating...

39:27.063 --> 39:28.264
I'll give you whatever you want.

39:28.898 --> 39:30.266
But you have to find out...

39:30.767 --> 39:33.703
where this Lee Jong Su is
and what he's doing now.

39:33.703 --> 39:35.037
Please make sure I get to meet him.

39:35.037 --> 39:36.806
Okay, deal!

39:36.806 --> 39:39.142
First, finding that bastard Lee Jong Su...

39:39.142 --> 39:40.176
is the key to this whole thing.

39:40.543 --> 39:42.779
By the way, is there anything
you want to ask me for?

39:42.779 --> 39:44.647
Say the word.
I'll throw it in as a freebie.

39:48.618 --> 39:49.786
Restore it, please.

39:50.052 --> 39:51.220
As fast as you can.

39:52.588 --> 39:54.390
This house is amazing.

39:54.390 --> 39:56.025
Even the slippers are cute.

39:57.293 --> 39:59.428
Myo Jin.

40:01.430 --> 40:02.999
I've missed you.

40:03.466 --> 40:04.700
It must've been hard.

40:04.967 --> 40:06.102
You went through a lot.

40:06.102 --> 40:07.804
Goodness,
look how thin your face has gotten.

40:08.271 --> 40:10.473
Have you been eating properly?

40:13.142 --> 40:14.877
We all know each other well.

40:14.877 --> 40:15.945
She's a good friend.

40:16.412 --> 40:19.715
She'll probably take
better care of you than I do.

40:20.450 --> 40:22.485
She's going to stay here with us
for a while.

40:22.985 --> 40:23.986
That's okay, right?

40:26.355 --> 40:29.125
Where was it that we met?

40:29.392 --> 40:30.293
What?

40:30.293 --> 40:31.661
You don't recognize me?

40:32.028 --> 40:33.796
You don't remember? I'm Ri A.

40:33.796 --> 40:35.598
You always said my name was pretty.

40:36.766 --> 40:38.334
We all traveled together,

40:38.334 --> 40:39.869
and we went hiking several times too.

40:40.603 --> 40:42.038
I see.

40:44.407 --> 40:46.242
No way, that ring.

40:47.243 --> 40:49.011
Did he propose?

40:49.011 --> 40:51.714
That's incredible.

40:52.482 --> 40:54.584
Ryu Jun Ho is famous...

40:54.584 --> 40:56.285
for being insanely picky about women.

40:56.285 --> 40:57.487
There she goes again.

40:57.653 --> 40:58.855
It's true.

40:58.855 --> 41:01.691
News anchors, models, business heiresses.

41:01.691 --> 41:03.192
Every woman who thought
she had a shot took one,

41:03.192 --> 41:05.161
and he turned every single one down.

41:05.161 --> 41:07.563
If people heard you,
they'd think it was all true.

41:07.563 --> 41:08.865
It is true, though.

41:11.400 --> 41:13.903
I'll head upstairs first.

41:14.237 --> 41:15.538
Okay.

41:15.538 --> 41:16.506
Go on up and rest.

41:28.851 --> 41:31.287
Isn't she worse off
than what you told me...

41:31.287 --> 41:32.188
if she's at that level?

41:32.188 --> 41:33.890
That's why I'm saying it's dangerous.

41:34.891 --> 41:36.559
You need to stay by her side
and watch her.

41:37.794 --> 41:40.429
Don't worry about anything else.
Just keep your promise.

41:50.273 --> 41:53.342
How long are they going
to keep living like this?

42:05.888 --> 42:07.256
Aren't you bored?

42:07.990 --> 42:10.960
I heard that ever since you got into
that accident when you went biking alone,

42:10.960 --> 42:12.462
you've basically been stuck at home.

42:13.563 --> 42:15.031
Right.

42:15.531 --> 42:17.433
I was being stubborn
and didn't listen to Jun Ho.

42:17.433 --> 42:19.102
Jun Ho had work,

42:19.102 --> 42:20.903
so he headed to the site
a little while ago.

42:20.903 --> 42:23.539
He asked me to make sure
you wouldn't get bored,

42:24.841 --> 42:26.442
and that just so happens
to be my specialty.

42:28.144 --> 42:29.479
No, it's okay.

42:29.679 --> 42:31.414
Please just go do your own thing, Ri A.

42:31.414 --> 42:32.882
Let's see.

42:32.882 --> 42:34.016
There it is.

42:35.751 --> 42:36.619
The car key.

42:37.086 --> 42:38.888
- Let's go.
- What?

42:39.589 --> 42:40.556
Go where?

42:40.790 --> 42:41.891
Just come with me.

42:42.425 --> 42:44.494
It's not somewhere
Jun Ho would be thrilled to hear about.

42:45.261 --> 42:46.195
Wait.

42:46.929 --> 42:48.297
If it's a place like that,
I don't want to go.

42:50.266 --> 42:52.101
You really have changed.

42:52.935 --> 42:53.669
What?

42:54.237 --> 42:56.539
Weren't you always the type
to act first and think later?

42:57.406 --> 42:59.242
I learned that
from watching you, you know.

43:10.219 --> 43:11.687
This is your car, Myo Jin.

43:11.687 --> 43:12.955
Do you want to try driving it yourself?

43:14.223 --> 43:16.259
That car is mine?

43:16.492 --> 43:17.527
Yes.

43:17.527 --> 43:18.995
Your old car...

43:18.995 --> 43:20.696
was totaled in the accident,

43:21.230 --> 43:23.466
and this one was something
Jun Ho bought for you as a discharge gift.

43:25.635 --> 43:27.870
I don't think I was very good at driving.

43:28.438 --> 43:30.239
You were basically a pro.

43:30.540 --> 43:32.442
I guess the accident
shook your confidence.

43:33.810 --> 43:35.044
Do you want to give it a try today?

43:36.112 --> 43:36.979
No.

43:38.948 --> 43:41.250
Okay. Then I'll drive today.

43:41.851 --> 43:42.685
Get in.

43:53.563 --> 43:55.798
Damn, this car is incredible.

43:56.132 --> 43:57.467
You're lucky, Myo Jin.

43:57.467 --> 43:59.502
What? Why?

43:59.502 --> 44:01.104
Your boyfriend's unreal.

44:01.537 --> 44:04.073
He's handsome, capable,
and makes crazy money.

44:04.507 --> 44:06.075
And on top of that,
he only has eyes for you.

44:06.476 --> 44:07.877
That's insane.

44:27.930 --> 44:28.764
Is that her?

44:29.699 --> 44:30.600
She's pretty.

44:30.900 --> 44:33.136
What's the point?
She's messed up in the head.

44:33.770 --> 44:35.004
That makes it better for us.

44:36.606 --> 44:38.007
What do you think
after seeing the estimate?

44:38.007 --> 44:38.975
Do you think the numbers look good?

44:40.243 --> 44:42.245
Let's each take one clean cut.

44:42.512 --> 44:44.614
I think that much
could come out pretty easy.

44:45.081 --> 44:45.948
You mean 100,000 dollars?

44:48.117 --> 44:49.519
Are we finally wiping out the debt?

44:50.286 --> 44:51.220
If this goes well.

44:51.654 --> 44:53.456
Hey, then let's squeeze
a little more while we're at it.

44:53.689 --> 44:54.991
It's not like chances like this
come around often.

44:54.991 --> 44:57.560
Things always fall apart
when you overdo it like that.

44:58.027 --> 44:59.529
Do you think
Ryu Jun Ho is some ordinary guy?

44:59.762 --> 45:01.063
Do you think connections are a joke?

45:02.932 --> 45:03.833
You're right.

45:07.503 --> 45:10.173
She goes to the hospital
or on simple errands by herself.

45:10.573 --> 45:13.309
She went out alone today too
and came back in the evening.

45:13.976 --> 45:15.244
Ryu Jun Ho's so busy...

45:15.244 --> 45:17.413
he doesn't seem to think much of that.

45:19.615 --> 45:20.750
That's our chance.

45:21.384 --> 45:23.119
I could do it right now.

45:23.119 --> 45:24.153
Are you kidding me?

45:24.420 --> 45:26.489
If that psycho gets kidnapped
the second I show up,

45:26.489 --> 45:28.057
who do you think
the police will suspect first?

45:29.559 --> 45:30.693
Do you think it'll take a while?

45:32.595 --> 45:33.496
No.

45:33.796 --> 45:35.631
Her mind's all over the place,

45:35.631 --> 45:36.833
so there should be plenty of chances.

46:04.127 --> 46:05.428
Hey, Ham Myo Jin.

46:06.062 --> 46:08.498
Why are you drinking alone? That's no fun.

46:09.265 --> 46:10.700
I'm fine.

46:11.267 --> 46:12.168
No, you're not.

46:13.536 --> 46:14.337
Let's go.

46:15.104 --> 46:16.839
Come on, hurry.

46:17.173 --> 46:18.641
- Come on.
- I said I'm fine.

46:22.445 --> 46:23.279
Come on.

47:28.511 --> 47:29.345
Hee Su!

47:43.993 --> 47:44.894
Darn it.

47:48.931 --> 47:49.999
Move.

47:49.999 --> 47:51.367
Move!

47:53.603 --> 47:55.772
My face.

47:55.772 --> 47:56.973
Look at you.

47:56.973 --> 47:59.675
Hey, I'm hurting just watching that.

48:01.310 --> 48:02.578
You little...

48:12.455 --> 48:13.289
What the...

48:14.023 --> 48:15.291
What's with her?

48:34.076 --> 48:35.545
You're dead today.

48:39.649 --> 48:41.217
That startled me.

48:41.217 --> 48:42.151
Hee Su.

48:42.852 --> 48:44.654
Do you want to join in too?

48:45.955 --> 48:47.256
That works for me.

48:52.962 --> 48:53.830
What?

48:56.365 --> 48:57.200
Shit.

48:57.867 --> 48:58.935
Are you insane?

48:59.368 --> 49:00.937
You need to bleed too.

49:09.378 --> 49:10.279
Hee Su.

49:10.279 --> 49:11.247
Get up.

49:12.815 --> 49:13.683
Choi Hee Su.

49:17.053 --> 49:17.987
Myo Jin.

49:25.394 --> 49:27.396
Get that away from me.

49:34.570 --> 49:35.338
Get up.

49:40.209 --> 49:41.043
What happened?

49:41.043 --> 49:42.678
My goodness. Blood.

49:43.312 --> 49:44.213
She's bleeding.

49:44.213 --> 49:45.481
- Isn't that blood?
- She's bleeding.

49:57.260 --> 49:58.094
Are you okay?

49:59.295 --> 50:00.263
It hurts so bad.

50:03.633 --> 50:04.534
Ham Myo Jin.

50:06.068 --> 50:07.136
Are you serious?

50:08.104 --> 50:09.672
Where does that kind of guts come from?

50:12.008 --> 50:13.276
When I get mad,

50:14.210 --> 50:15.445
I sometimes lose it.

50:17.046 --> 50:18.881
But still,

50:19.182 --> 50:20.650
weren't you scared back there?

50:20.917 --> 50:22.885
Scared? Please.

50:22.885 --> 50:24.187
You were in that state.

50:24.187 --> 50:25.922
I had to fight
like my life depended on it.

50:28.658 --> 50:31.294
Damn those bastards.

50:31.661 --> 50:32.995
I thought I was going to die.

50:34.764 --> 50:36.299
Why did you do that back there?

50:37.166 --> 50:38.901
Did you think I was going to stab you?

50:39.135 --> 50:40.069
It's just,

50:40.636 --> 50:42.071
I can't handle sharp things.

50:42.405 --> 50:43.372
What?

50:44.006 --> 50:45.074
It's hereditary.

50:45.575 --> 50:46.876
My dad's exactly the same.

50:48.244 --> 50:50.146
You're just like a little kid.

50:51.047 --> 50:52.748
Do I have to keep
protecting you like this?

51:01.757 --> 51:02.658
Why?

51:03.025 --> 51:04.127
Why do you look like that?

51:04.760 --> 51:05.695
I'm mad.

51:07.263 --> 51:09.532
Even if we report them to the police,

51:09.532 --> 51:11.134
they'll be out again in no time.

51:11.701 --> 51:12.702
Don't worry.

51:14.303 --> 51:16.105
I already told my dad everything.

51:18.274 --> 51:20.309
Didn't you say he was overseas right now?

51:21.010 --> 51:22.912
I didn't tell him to come back.

51:22.912 --> 51:24.914
I told him to send people
and get it handled.

51:27.416 --> 51:28.918
You made him worried.

51:30.086 --> 51:31.487
Did he say when he was coming back?

51:33.322 --> 51:36.659
There are people everywhere
trying to squeeze money out of him,

51:38.327 --> 51:41.097
and that's why he tries
not to come back much.

51:42.698 --> 51:43.900
My dad...

51:44.700 --> 51:47.537
is some self-made chairman
of a major corporation for everyone else.

51:49.872 --> 51:51.073
But to me,

51:51.741 --> 51:53.676
he's just an ordinary old man...

51:53.676 --> 51:55.077
who's already well past
the twilight of his life,

51:57.947 --> 51:59.849
and who'll spend the rest of it...

51:59.849 --> 52:01.717
suffering because he has
a delinquent daughter like me.

52:13.830 --> 52:16.332
(Powerful business family's villa
explosion caused by gas leak)

52:16.332 --> 52:18.000
(Chairman Choi Young Ho of Mono Group...)

52:18.000 --> 52:19.669
(and his only blood relative,
Ms. Choi, have died.)

52:25.041 --> 52:26.642
(Mono Group Chairman Choi Young Ho...)

52:26.642 --> 52:28.111
(and Ms. Choi were found dead
in the blast.)

52:28.111 --> 52:30.847
(Police said they are also leaving open
the possibility of arson.)

52:38.554 --> 52:40.656
(Hanguk Somang Hospital)

52:48.464 --> 52:49.332
Thank you.

52:56.305 --> 52:57.406
It's unusual.

52:58.207 --> 53:01.377
Honestly, I prefer tea to coffee.

53:01.611 --> 53:03.513
I don't recommend coffee either.

53:04.213 --> 53:07.250
The effects of caffeine
don't really suit my work.

53:07.517 --> 53:08.518
You're truly...

53:09.385 --> 53:10.486
very meticulous.

53:11.921 --> 53:14.257
That's probably why...

53:15.324 --> 53:17.193
I've always trusted you, Dr. Jung.

53:18.761 --> 53:20.029
Actually,

53:20.396 --> 53:21.464
has Myo Jin...

53:23.232 --> 53:26.903
ever mentioned a friend named Choi Hee Su?

53:27.403 --> 53:28.304
No.

53:28.571 --> 53:30.373
That's the first time
I've heard that name.

53:31.774 --> 53:34.277
I see. She said she learned about her...

53:34.277 --> 53:37.280
from a friend she ran into by chance
at the hospital.

53:38.714 --> 53:42.418
Maybe she just hasn't
mentioned it to you yet.

53:42.685 --> 53:44.587
She seemed very curious about her with me.

53:45.121 --> 53:46.823
Do you know her?

53:47.490 --> 53:49.025
Then I suppose she'd ask.

53:49.258 --> 53:52.428
I only told her what little I remembered.

53:52.428 --> 53:54.964
She wasn't that important a friend.

53:59.268 --> 54:00.903
This may be an improper question,

54:01.904 --> 54:03.439
but during treatment,

54:04.173 --> 54:05.975
is it possible for a patient to lie?

54:06.676 --> 54:09.812
If someone's in a situation
where the line between real memory...

54:11.280 --> 54:12.915
and illusion is blurred,

54:12.915 --> 54:15.318
I thought it could definitely happen.

54:15.518 --> 54:16.953
It's not impossible,

54:16.953 --> 54:18.821
but it's not something
that can be judged lightly.

54:19.789 --> 54:22.125
Calling what a patient says a lie...

54:22.125 --> 54:24.894
is a one-sided view
held by the person listening.

54:26.796 --> 54:28.264
Then what if the patient...

54:28.264 --> 54:30.800
knows that they're lying?

54:31.267 --> 54:32.835
Isn't that...

54:33.903 --> 54:35.071
a different matter?

54:35.471 --> 54:37.573
Unless the patient says so directly,

54:38.841 --> 54:41.711
that, too, isn't something
we can judge carelessly.

54:42.345 --> 54:43.212
Doctor.

54:44.447 --> 54:45.948
Are my questions...

54:49.552 --> 54:50.686
making you uncomfortable?

54:51.287 --> 54:52.188
Pardon?

54:52.188 --> 54:54.657
Coming here out of the blue...

54:54.657 --> 54:56.859
to ask about a friend
who doesn't even seem that important,

54:58.094 --> 55:00.530
and asking if the patient might be lying.

55:01.631 --> 55:02.765
Even I can see...

55:03.933 --> 55:06.402
how that could catch you off guard.

55:08.137 --> 55:09.539
This isn't a normal situation.

55:11.674 --> 55:13.609
I've been struggling with it.

55:14.343 --> 55:16.746
But this isn't something
I can just let slide,

55:16.746 --> 55:18.748
so I'm asking you directly.

55:19.315 --> 55:20.349
Myo Jin...

55:22.518 --> 55:24.454
is acting out of character.

55:25.521 --> 55:27.924
I don't believe
it's anything to be concerned about.

55:28.858 --> 55:30.626
A patient's words and actions...

55:31.227 --> 55:33.463
can appear irregular and contradictory.

55:39.769 --> 55:42.505
Trusting and waiting
isn't as easy as it sounds.

55:43.706 --> 55:45.241
It can be tedious and frustrating.

55:46.576 --> 55:49.745
Especially for a guardian
who wants the patient to recover...

55:49.745 --> 55:51.314
as soon as possible.

55:55.218 --> 55:56.486
Really?

56:04.193 --> 56:05.962
Then I suppose...

56:06.329 --> 56:07.530
there are only two possibilities.

56:10.566 --> 56:12.935
Either I'm not qualified
to be her guardian,

56:14.837 --> 56:15.838
or you, Dr. Jung,

56:19.809 --> 56:21.210
are lying.

57:05.371 --> 57:10.123
(REVERSE)

57:10.493 --> 57:12.528
Why haven't you told me until now...

57:12.528 --> 57:13.763
about Hee Su
and your relationship, Jun Ho?

57:14.063 --> 57:15.164
Why did you do that?

57:15.164 --> 57:16.466
You didn't forget, did you?

57:16.732 --> 57:20.036
I'm not giving you this gift for nothing.

57:20.336 --> 57:22.772
I'm out of patience now.

57:22.772 --> 57:24.941
I don't even know what I'll do.

57:24.941 --> 57:25.808
You bastard.

57:26.375 --> 57:28.177
If both of them are avoiding me,

57:28.177 --> 57:29.812
then I must be involved somehow.

57:30.113 --> 57:31.981
How reckless of you to come here.

57:32.315 --> 57:34.250
By the time you realize it,
it'll already be too late.

57:34.717 --> 57:36.586
So watch yourself.

57:38.301 --> 57:40.301
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
